# Backend Rules

> Extends [root AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md). Auto-loaded when editing `*.controller.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.module.ts`, `*.worker.ts`.

## Always

- Use `@platform-core/logger` (`log.*`, `httpContext`, `loggerMiddleWare`) — never `console.*`. [MUST]
- Extract `locationId` from `req.user.locationId` or `authContext.locationId`. [MUST]
- Use IAM v2 (`@platform-core/iam-v2`) helpers or guards on routes that access tenant data. [MUST]
- Implement `onModuleDestroy` and close connections on graceful shutdown. [SHOULD]
- Extend `BaseWorker` for platform worker implementations. [SHOULD]

## Never

- Never use `console.log`, `console.warn`, or `console.error` in service files. [MUST]
- Never trust `locationId` from client request body, query, or params. [MUST]
- Never put business logic in controllers — delegate to services. [SHOULD]
- Never access the database directly from a controller. [SHOULD]

## Prefer

- Prefer constructor injection over property injection for dependencies.
- Prefer `async/await` over callback-style async patterns.
- Prefer explicit error types (`BadRequestException`, `NotFoundException`) over generic throws.
- Prefer small, single-responsibility services (<200 lines).
- Prefer the matching framework overlay for backend-specific rules (`nestjs`, `go-connect`).

## Verify

- Run `npm run test` before marking backend work complete.
- Confirm no `console.*` calls remain in changed service files.

